India 10-Year Bonds Fall for Fourth Day on Interest Rate Outlook

-- B y   J e a n e t t e   R o d r i g u e s
-- 
2011-10-24T03:44:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-24/india-10-year-bonds-fall-for-fourth-day-on-interest-rate-outlook.html
India ’s 10-year bonds declined for a
fourth day on speculation the central bank will boost borrowing
costs tomorrow for the seventh time this year to cool inflation.  The yield on the 7.8 percent government security due April
2021 climbed two basis points, 0.02 percentage point, to 8.84
percent at 9:12 a.m. in  Mumbai , according to the central bank’s
trading system.  To contact the reporter on this story:
